DIV1.P:
Indeed the praises of God were now her daily employ, and she never appeared happier than when engaged in this heavenly exercise. She


frequently sang with transport the following words,

"Now I'll sing of Jesu's merit,

"Tell the world of his dear name;

"That if any want his Spirit,

"Jesus is the very same;

"He that asketh soon receiveth;

"He that seeks is sure to find;

"Come—for whosoe'er believeth,

"He will never cast behind."
